Privacy Policy

**Data We Collect**

- Guild IDs
- Channel IDs
- User IDs
- Command / Message Content


**Why do we need the following data? How is it used?**

Guild IDs are stored upon the Bot joining your Guild. The Data is used to uniquely distinquish all Guilds.

Channel and User IDs are stored upon command interaction (when a command is being used). This is used to track the Bot's activity, linking the User and Channel together based on the interaction.

Message Content is stored upon command interaction. The content is sliced therefore, only the command name is collected.


** How long is the Data used?**

Guild IDs are stored upon the Bot being added to that Guild and until removable.

Channel IDs are stored temporarily; the data will be removed within a week (7 days) of usage.

User IDs are stored temporarily; the data will be removed within 3 days.

Command Interactions (Message Content) are stored indefinitely.


** Data Removal **

Please email shiftsinquires@gmail.com to request having your data deleted from our services. Please be sure to specifically indicate what data you would like removed. Response times may vary and could take up to 3 weeks or more.

Requesting your Data to be removed also results in a termination of being able to use the bot, this is done to comply with your request.

** Data Requests**

Please email shiftsinquires@gmail.com to request all of your data or specifics. Please keep in mind ownership of you owning your Discord Account, Guild, etc, is required. Response time may vary and could take up to 2 weeks or more.

** Changes to our Privacy Policy **

We reserve the right to update this privacy policy at any time without notice. Continuation to use our services after any changes will mean that you must agree and be in full in accordance with our policy. Violations of our policy may result in permanent banishments across all of our services.


** Understanding Terms **

Guild - Represents a Discord Server with an collection of users, channels, etc.

ID - An 18-digit number that uniquely indentifies a Discord property.

User - A Member who uses the Bot.

Bot - Artificial intelligent instances that perform automated tasks. (Randomizer#8461)


